Subject: [PATCH 2/3] MIPS: SMP: Allow suspend and hibernation to be selected.

On SMP their implementation depends on CPU hotplugging code which is now
available.

Signed-off-by: Ralf Baechle <ralf.baechle@windriver.com>

 arch/mips/Kconfig |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)
---
 arch/mips/Kconfig |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/mips/Kconfig b/arch/mips/Kconfig
index d0d6ff3..5e3ab38 100644
--- a/arch/mips/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/mips/Kconfig
@@ -2044,7 +2044,7 @@ menu "Power management options"
 
 config ARCH_SUSPEND_POSSIBLE
 	def_bool y
-	depends on !SMP
+	depends on SYS_SUPPORTS_HOTPLUG_CPU
 
 source "kernel/power/Kconfig"
 
